    "ideation": "The Last Quarter Moon represents the transition from full presence to total shadow. This performance personifies the moon as a celestial observer caught in a perpetual slow rotation between light and dark. The acting is defined by a slow, orbital gaze and a dramatic shift in color—moving from a bright, lunar silver to a deep, void-like indigo. The eyes act as the terminator line: as one side dims and narrows (the shadow taking over), the other remains watchful. The mouth is the 'solar wind,' a slow-rolling wave that carries the face through its phases. The sequence ends in a heavy, contemplative lopsidedness, capturing the feeling of waning away into the night.",
